                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13992546" author="jrottinghuis" created="Thu, 8 May 2014 07:23:21 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Why not simply default this to hadoop.tmp.dir ?&lt;br/&gt;
True that hadoop.tmp.dir often has variables in it itself (for example /tmp/hadoop-$&lt;/p&gt;
{user}
&lt;p&gt;) however, if pig.temp.dir cannot directly refer to hadoop.tmp.dir then both need to be kept in sync by hand ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995329" author="aniket486" created="Mon, 12 May 2014 18:55:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jrottinghuis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jrottinghuis&quot;&gt;Joep Rottinghuis&lt;/a&gt;, that means we assume that pig alway runs on hadoop (which is sort of true). Also, removing pig.temp.dir will not be backwards compatible.&lt;br/&gt;
Unfortunately, Configuration#substituteVars is not declared public (and static), so copying would be the only option left to enable this. Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13996791" author="aniket486" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 20:11:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I have attached &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3929&quot; title=&quot;pig.temp.dir should allow to substitute vars as hadoop configuration does&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3929&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3929&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-1.patch and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3929&quot; title=&quot;pig.temp.dir should allow to substitute vars as hadoop configuration does&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3929&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3929&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-2.patch with two different approaches. Comments?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13996998" author="jcoveney" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 23:36:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aniket486&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aniket486&quot;&gt;Aniket Mokashi&lt;/a&gt;: I assume that hadoop applies the substituteVars when it does the conversion to the Configuration? If that&apos;s the case that seems like a fine approach, since it means we&apos;ll be consistent with how hadoop does it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13997825" author="aniket486" created="Wed, 14 May 2014 18:56:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hadoop does substituteVars on conf.get.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jcoveney&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jcoveney&quot;&gt;Jonathan Coveney&lt;/a&gt;, Which one do you prefer? 1. props to conf 2. copying substituteVars.&lt;br/&gt;
converting props to conf has one downside- it makes pig internal code path depend on hadoop.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13998365" author="jcoveney" created="Thu, 15 May 2014 02:34:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, would be nice to avoid that dependency if we can. I&apos;m +1 approach 1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14003810" author="aniket486" created="Tue, 20 May 2014 19:44:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk. Thanks for the review, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jcoveney&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jcoveney&quot;&gt;Jonathan Coveney&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
